    <name>Session #5 Assignment A: Develop Parts1-3 of EI Lesson for Content Learning</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style="float: left; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="Assignment icon - hand writing in notebook" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LTA-EI-Assignmenticon.jpg" height="64" width="75" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For this assignment, we ask that you use what you have learned about EI lesson planning for content learning and the use of graphic organizers to begin a new lesson plan&lt;/strong&gt; – the introduction, explanation and modeling sections.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Steps to Complete this Assignment:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using your reflections on graphic organizers as well as the EI Lesson Planning resources linked below, develop the first two parts of an EI Lesson for content learning (Introduction and Explanation/Modeling steps).  To complete this step, we recommend that you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify a concept or key vocabulary words that are important for your learners to know.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Select a graphic organizer format that matches how you want learners to interact with the content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop your blank and completed graphic organizer examples.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plan how you will introduce the lesson (set up new learning).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plan how you will explain and model the graphic organizer to your learners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optional: Try out your introduction, explain and Model steps with a student or colleague (and make adjustments based on their feedback).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Submit your initial plan to your facilitator.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Click on the Add Submission button below, and then upload your plan or enter it into the box below (or paste). Feel free to add any reflections or thoughts you have on this process in the box as well. &lt;span style="color: #ff0000;"&gt;Remember to click on the Save button!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We strongly encourage you to SAVE a digital copy of your lesson plan locally  before submitting it.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EI Lesson Planning Resources:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LtAEI-S1-EI_Lesson_Plan_Outline%20%281%29.pdf"&gt;Explicit Instruction Plan Outline.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" title="Example: Hamburger Writing EI Lesson Plan Parts 1 &amp;amp; 2" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LtAEI-S5b-Hamburger-lesson-plan-pt1-2.pdf"&gt;Example: Hamburger Writing EI Lesson Plan Parts 1 &amp;amp; 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Once you have submitted your plan:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Click on an "Explicit Instruction" link at the top (or at left under "my Courses") &lt;/strong&gt;to return to the Main Course Outline and access the next course activity.&lt;/p&gt;
